Hi, really nice to meet you. Sorry for gramatical errors, english is not my first language. Mods will probably delete this, but I just want to speak what I have in heart. So, I saw your post one day ago, and it stayed in my mind because Im too 15. I had I guess a rough few years. I had really bad OCD although undiagnosed, but it was bad belive me. I was showering for an hour and my skin would peel. I had rituals let's call them to complete in order to go with my day so forth so forth. I also had really bad anxiety, I wasnt really leaving my house, I was scared. And biggest thing is I thought I was trans. I live in a small country in Europe. So being trans is not as normal as in modern countries. My parents are also not belivers in the treatment of transgender people. So me becoming a woman so to say never happened and right now Im just a guy. I write this because I think that transitioning into a woman would be bad for me, and honnestly and I know I cant think for you but  I dont think that this is a path that will lead you to satisfaction. I think being transgender is a mental problem, having feeling of being uncomfortable in one's own body and I think that in most cases that feeling has reasons. For me they were want to escape my old life filled with saddnes, pain and simply boredom. Becoming a woman was really exciting, new and fun to me. Id guess its same for you. Ive done extensive research about being transgender, well I thought I was one. And from what I can tell it isn't just fun and games. I think that treatment for trans people is completely wrong, If you have a mental disorder, lets say schizophrenia, you wouldn't hire actors to make those people episodes real, you would treat those people so they dont have episodes. Im trying to tell that its much better to treat gender dysphoria by actually treating gender dysphoria rather than trying to match the body to the perception in the mind. Now, what really stood in the picture is your overal facial expression. Im sorry but Im honest. The way you act on the camera is feminine. I dont want to make you dysphoric as I know that its painfull. I just want to tell you my point. I think its way more harmfull to affirm than to tell the truth. Because, sad truth is that nobody can run away from reality. And the sooner we accept it, no matter how painfull, it will give us a stable platform from which to grow. Im gonna tell you I have commented on ConsumeProduct, the sub that many consider hatefull, as I dont like materialism. I have outmost compasion for trans people because I know they are strugling but I think the whole worldview on this issue is wrong. If you read this to the end you made me incredibly happy, thank you. If you want to pm me I'd be happy, I didn't want to send this directily because I didnt want to be pushy. I hope mods dont delete this, I hope I wasn't transphobic. Well I wish you the best of luck, and I wish you happy and loving life.

Did you ever hear the tragedy of Darth Plagueis The Wise? I thought not. It’s not a story the Jedi would tell you. It’s a Sith legend. Darth Plagueis was a Dark Lord of the Sith, so powerful and so wise he could use the Force to influence the midichlorians to create life… He had such a knowledge of the dark side that he could even keep the ones he cared about from dying. The dark side of the Force is a pathway to many abilities some consider to be unnatural. He became so powerful… the only thing he was afraid of was losing his power, which eventually, of course, he did. Unfortunately, he taught his apprentice everything he knew, then his apprentice killed him in his sleep. Ironic. He could save others from death, but not himself.
